# Node Api project skeleton!!

## Environment Requirements:
1. install latest version of node LTE,
2. install npm


## Getting started:
1. npm install
2. npm start -> run the project
3. npm test -> test the project

##Help to npm start to run the apis in postman
1. POST-login
-localhost:3000/api/user/user/login
-body = {
	"username" :"anything",
	"password" :"anything"
	}

Result -> this will return a timeout based token for next two apis

2. POST- json-patch
-localhost:3000/api/jsonpatch/jsonpatch/jsonpatching
-headers= token{from previous step}
-body= {
		"doc" : {"foo": [1, 3]},
		"patchObj": [{"op": "add", "path": "/foo/1", "value": 2}]
	}
Result -> {
	    "patch": {
	        "foo": [
	            1,
	            2,
	            3
	        ]
	    }
	}

3. POST-thumbnail-creator
-localhost:3000/api/thumbnail/thumbnail/createThumbnail

-headers = token {same as prrevious step}

-body -> {
		"url": "https://www.google.com/images/srpr/logo3w.png"
	}

Result -> it will download the image in images folder and create thumbnail in the same folder
